The paper discusses a learning-based approach to optimize the performance of OWL reasoners, which involves selecting the appropriate expansion-ordering heuristics for each ontology. This involves analyzing the syntactic structure and other features of the ontologies, which suggests a connection to natural language processing (cs.CL) and deep learning (cs.DL). The use of machine learning to optimize performance also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the focus on optimizing the performance of reasoners suggests a connection to software engineering (cs.SE).
